Docs.summary: A Pool in the Azure Batch service.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AllocationState As Nullable(Of AllocationState)

Docs.summary: Whether the Pool is resizing.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AllocationStateTransitionTime As Nullable(Of DateTimeOffset)

Docs.summary: The time at which the Pool entered its current allocation state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ApplicationPackageReferences As IReadOnlyList(Of BatchApplicationPackageReference)

Docs.summary: The list of Packages to be installed on each Compute Node in the Pool. Changes to Package references affect all new Nodes joining the Pool, but do not affect Compute Nodes that are already in the Pool until they are rebooted or reimaged. There is a maximum of 10 Package references on any given Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AutoScaleEvaluationInterval As Nullable(Of TimeSpan)

Docs.summary: The time interval at which to automatically adjust the Pool size according to the autoscale formula. This property is set only if the Pool automatically scales, i.e. enableAutoScale is true.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AutoScaleFormula As String

Docs.summary: A formula for the desired number of Compute Nodes in the Pool. This property is set only if the Pool automatically scales, i.e. enableAutoScale is true.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property AutoScaleRun As AutoScaleRun

Docs.summary: The results and errors from the last execution of the autoscale formula. This property is set only if the Pool automatically scales, i.e. enableAutoScale is true.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CreationTime As Nullable(Of DateTimeOffset)

Docs.summary: The creation time of the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CurrentDedicatedNodes As Nullable(Of Integer)

Docs.summary: The number of dedicated Compute Nodes currently in the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CurrentLowPriorityNodes As Nullable(Of Integer)

Docs.summary: The number of Spot/Low-priority Compute Nodes currently in the Pool. Spot/Low-priority Compute Nodes which have been preempted are included in this count.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property CurrentNodeCommunicationMode As Nullable(Of BatchNodeCommunicationMode)

Docs.summary: The current state of the pool communication mode.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property DisplayName As String

Docs.summary: The display name for the Pool. The display name need not be unique and can contain any Unicode characters up to a maximum length of 1024.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EnableAutoScale As Nullable(Of Boolean)

Docs.summary: Whether the Pool size should automatically adjust over time. If false, at least one of targetDedicatedNodes and targetLowPriorityNodes must be specified. If true, the autoScaleFormula property is required and the Pool automatically resizes according to the formula. The default value is false.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property EnableInterNodeCommunication As Nullable(Of Boolean)

Docs.summary: Whether the Pool permits direct communication between Compute Nodes. This imposes restrictions on which Compute Nodes can be assigned to the Pool. Specifying this value can reduce the chance of the requested number of Compute Nodes to be allocated in the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ETag As String

Docs.summary: The ETag of the Pool. This is an opaque string. You can use it to detect whether the Pool has changed between requests. In particular, you can be pass the ETag when updating a Pool to specify that your changes should take effect only if nobody else has modified the Pool in the meantime.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Id As String

Docs.summary: A string that uniquely identifies the Pool within the Account. The ID can contain any combination of alphanumeric characters including hyphens and underscores, and cannot contain more than 64 characters. The ID is case-preserving and case-insensitive (that is, you may not have two IDs within an Account that differ only by case).

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Identity As BatchPoolIdentity

Docs.summary: The identity of the Batch pool, if configured. The list of user identities associated with the Batch pool. The user identity dictionary key references will be ARM resource ids in the form: '/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.ManagedIdentity/userAssignedIdentities/{identityName}'.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property LastModified As Nullable(Of DateTimeOffset)

Docs.summary: The last modified time of the Pool. This is the last time at which the Pool level data, such as the targetDedicatedNodes or enableAutoscale settings, changed. It does not factor in node-level changes such as a Compute Node changing state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Metadata As IReadOnlyList(Of MetadataItem)

Docs.summary: A list of name-value pairs associated with the Pool as metadata.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property MountConfiguration As IReadOnlyList(Of MountConfiguration)

Docs.summary: A list of file systems to mount on each node in the pool. This supports Azure Files, NFS, CIFS/SMB, and Blobfuse.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property NetworkConfiguration As NetworkConfiguration

Docs.summary: The network configuration for the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ResizeErrors As IReadOnlyList(Of ResizeError)

Docs.summary: A list of errors encountered while performing the last resize on the Pool. This property is set only if one or more errors occurred during the last Pool resize, and only when the Pool allocationState is Steady.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ResizeTimeout As Nullable(Of TimeSpan)

Docs.summary: The timeout for allocation of Compute Nodes to the Pool. This is the timeout for the most recent resize operation. (The initial sizing when the Pool is created counts as a resize.) The default value is 15 minutes.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property ResourceTags As IReadOnlyDictionary(Of String, String)

Docs.summary: The user-specified tags associated with the pool. The user-defined tags to be associated with the Azure Batch Pool. When specified, these tags are propagated to the backing Azure resources associated with the pool. This property can only be specified when the Batch account was created with the poolAllocationMode property set to 'UserSubscription'.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property StartTask As BatchStartTask

Docs.summary: A Task specified to run on each Compute Node as it joins the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property State As Nullable(Of BatchPoolState)

Docs.summary: The current state of the Pool.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property StateTransitionTime As Nullable(Of DateTimeOffset)

Docs.summary: The time at which the Pool entered its current state.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property Stats As BatchPoolStatistics

Docs.summary: Utilization and resource usage statistics for the entire lifetime of the Pool. This property is populated only if the CloudPool was retrieved with an expand clause including the 'stats' attribute; otherwise it is null. The statistics may not be immediately available. The Batch service performs periodic roll-up of statistics. The typical delay is about 30 minutes.
